  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assisting Returnees in Sila (ARIS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rural populations</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is located in the Sila region of Chad. The Sila district is highly susceptible to natural hazards and conflict, compounded by poor governance and under-development. World Concern has been working with IDP&#x2019;s and Sudanese refugees in the Sila district since 2006, with the long-term goal of building resilient communities in this region. World Concern has introduced displaced people to livelihood diversification opportunities, water and sanitation management, and increased economic opportunities.  The two objectives of this project are: 1) to increase food security in thirty communities and 2) to increase access to credit for vulnerable households.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022; Improve access to food through increased food production for sale and consumption (livestock and agricultural production)

&#x2022; Increase immediate income thorugh restored access to productive assets and capital

&#x2022; Increased access to credit for vulnerable households</narrative>
  </description>
